value: Breeds in the high north on Spitsbergen, New Siberian Islands, arctic coast of Siberia from the Taimyr Peninsula to the mouth of the Lena, arctic islands north of North America, Southampton Island and northern Greenland. Russian ornithologists believe that an isolated colony nests on the shores of the salt lakes in the Aralo-Caspian desert. Winters from the British Isles, the North Sea, India, China, Japan, central California, the Gulf coast and Virginia, south to Cape Colony, Madagascar, Malay Archipelago, Australia, islands in the South Pacific, southern Chile (Chiloe Island) and southern Argentina.

value: Aus, Indon, NCal, PNG, Sol, Aureed, Kodall, Ugar, New Guinea, Amadee, Beautemps­Beaupré, Canard, Carrey, Contrariete, Double, Grande Terre, Ile Des Pins, Maitre, Pouh, Ti'Ambouenne, Bougainville, Buka, New Britain, New Guinea, Gizo, Leorava, Reef, Santa Isabel, Three Sisters
Palearctic winter visitor, coastal areas: all around coast of continent and islands; vagrant inland.
barren tundra, migrn sandy beaches, mudflats

Dry sedge, barren, or stony tundra, but generally near water (breeding); primarily sandy beaches, less frequently on mudflats, bare shores of lakes or rivers, jetties, and rocky seacoasts (nonbreeding).
